---
A dynamic CLI for Atlassian Cloud

Usage: shrug.exe [OPTIONS] [COMMAND]

Commands:
  jira           Jira Cloud operations
  jira-software  Jira Software operations (boards, sprints, backlogs)
  confluence     Confluence operations
  auth           Authentication management (set-token, status)
  profile        Profile management (create, list, show, delete, use)
  cache          Cache management (refresh specs)
  help           Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
  -o, --output <OUTPUT>      Output format [default: table] [possible values: json, table, csv]
      --color <COLOR>        Color output [default: auto] [possible values: auto, always, never]
  -p, --profile <PROFILE>    Configuration profile to use
  -v, --verbose...           Increase verbosity (-v, -vv, -vvv for trace)
  -n, --dry-run              Dry run — show what would happen without making changes
  -L, --limit <LIMIT>        Maximum number of results to fetch (implies pagination)
      --pager                Pipe output through a pager (e.g., less)
  -q, --quiet                Suppress non-essential output
      --jql <JQL>            Raw JQL query string (Jira/Jira Software only)
      --project <PROJECT>    JQL shorthand: filter by project key
      --assignee <ASSIGNEE>  JQL shorthand: filter by assignee ("me" for current user)
      --status <STATUS>      JQL shorthand: filter by status
      --type <TYPE>          JQL shorthand: filter by issue type
      --priority <PRIORITY>  JQL shorthand: filter by priority
      --label <LABEL>        JQL shorthand: filter by label
  -h, --help                 Print help
  -V, --version              Print version
